        <body>
            <p>See B K</p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Richmond</placeName>
                <date>February 28, 1830</date>
            </p>
            <p>My dear <addressee>Isaac</addressee></p>
            <p>I R<hi rend="sup">d</hi> your <sic>Last</sic> letter. I see the <add>?</add> to
                printing your books<lb/> is much more than you wrote to me before as I know you will
                not<lb/> publish it without some <sic>prosback</sic> of gaining something by it I
                will<lb/> say nothing now on the subject but I <sic>Leave</sic> it to your
                    <sic>judgement</sic> to<lb/> do with it as you please. I would take 20 or 30
                copies of it as so<lb/> soon as they are printed but that would be a poor chance for
                the<lb/> rest, I wish you <sic>Could</sic> do it with some assurance of gain<lb/>
                how ever if not at present I am sure in some short time you may be<lb/>
                <sic>aboe</sic> to do it to advantage. I saw <persName>Mr. Mordecai</persName> last
                week he said<lb/> he would take a Copy but said nothing <sic>Else</sic> he has not
                called here<lb/> for 2 <sic>Months</sic>. We are all well, hope you are better of
                your <sic>Cold</sic><lb/> no news.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I remain your <del>friend</del> affectionate Uncle <persName
                    role="author">Zalma Rehina</persName><lb/> Your Aunt &amp; <persName>Mrs De
                    Pass</persName>
                <persName>Rein</persName>
                <persName>Abby </persName>and all your friends send<lb/> their love to you. Remember
                me <sic>kindlt</sic> to <persName>Mr. &amp; Mrs. Peixotto</persName><lb/> and the
                young <persName>Lyndes</persName> and all my friends in
                    <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName><lb/>
                <persName>Mrs Sol Marks</persName>
                <sic>Desires</sic> to be remembered to you</p>
        </body>
